 daemon
 emulation lib



Build 
-----
  ./tools/bootstrap.sh      (optional, you need tools - read HACKING)
  ./configure --prefix=...  (by default: /tmp/$USER/confi)
  make
  make install 
  
See also Makefile.globals - you can define
  $(CFLAGS_EXTRA) 
  $(LDFLAGS_EXTRA)

One such define is ONE_SHOT for debugging purposes - to suppress forking 
and threading.



Install
-------
  make install 

By default, ir will install in /tmp/$USER/lincs.  Use --prefix options of the
configure script to change those defaults.

(FIXME: will change in the future to these):
    -configuration data   under /etc/confi/entries
    -confi binaries       under /etc/confi/bin
    -confi log            under /var/??
    -confi development 
        -headers          under /usr/include/lincs
        -libs             under /usr/lib/lincs

In a normal installation, one should create first a user named lincs and 
install the package as user lincs.  Then modify the lincs user account as to 
have no shell and no home (so that if the lincs system breaks, root cannot be 
compromised, much like user man, daemon, etc. under Debian). 

Have binaries owned by root and runnable by any user and entries/ owned by 
lincs user (readable by any?).  

Start scripts have to be modified to automatically start the cfgs_configd 
daemon and to preload the libemul.so emulating /etc files (FIXME).



Tests
-----
  cd tests && make check => tests/run_tests
OR
  make test

Note: make check fails for expat because it needs some extra packages installed,
hence the 'make test'.  

Read also: 
  tests/tests.config 
  tests/get_set_rm_val.tst
        libemul.tst
      
Tests not included in the test harness:
  daemon_stress
  daemon_signal 
    

